==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*στέφανος / stephanos / stef'-an-os

===Etymology===
*From an apparently primary “stepho” (to twine or wreathe); a chaplet (as a badge of royalty, a prize in the public games or a symbol of honor generally; but more conspicuous and elaborate than the simple fillet,  [[διάδημα]] {{GG|1238}}), literally or figuratively: 

===Noun===
'''στέφανος'''

# [[crown]].

